title: For Sale:  Pre-Ban M1A All USGI w/ Ultra-Rare USMC DMR Scope Mount
postcontent:
This is a 1993 produced rifle with every part being USGI, except for the Springfield Armory receiver. USGI parts are highly sought after by M1A enthusists. These USGI parts include:
Winchester Apr. 1963 produced barrel (Chrome lined and mirror bright)
HRA marked Op rod
HRT bolt
BME and WC rear sight assembly
HR Trigger assembly with a mix of SA and HR parts. 
USGI front site with bayonet lug

The rarest of the USGI parts on this rifle is the GG&G US Marine Corps scope mount. These were built for the USMC when they brought the M14 out of the warehouses and began using them for designated marksman rifles. There are pictures online from Marines using them on duty in Iraq and Afghanistan and also in the 90's. These were built specifically for the USMC as noted by that on the scope mount. A handful were sold to private individuals by GG&G at some point during the run. So few were sold that a prominent M14 book stated none were sold to the public, and was edited to show the opposite on future editions. The name of the book escapes me, or I would have written it for completeness. 

So what this rifle is, is as near an original copy as possible to an issued M14 from the early Vietnam war as possible without changing the receiver. And it gets even better than that when you add the USMC scope mount. It then becomes the closest copy of the M14 as it re-entered active service with the Marine Corps as a designated marksman rifle.

For the full price it comes with everything in picture one; USGI wood stock, a USGI fiberglass stock with the selector switch hole filled in my Springfield Armory, current USGI sling, 4 new unused USGI Checkmate Industries 20 round M14 magazines, 1 5 round Checkmate Industries magazine, and a 1990's chinese M14 magazine (which has been flawless), and all the tools shown to dis/reassemble the rifle. The rifle has been shimmed and worked on to increase the accuracy. It is a great shooter, and I really do not need to sell/trade the rifle, but I want to start another project. 

Also open to offers.
